"UsbCommandLayerUbuntu" stores all possible access to ROS
packages. It passes function names called by "JacoAPI" to DSP on
robot. In "JacoAPI", it is imported in binary format. "JocoComm" can
be considered as the starting point to implement ROS and other
basic functions. ROS node is created and ROS logs are generously
used. Fundamental functions and api operations are defined here.
